## 9. Findings & recommendations

### 9.1 What works well

1. **Hard/legal compliance is rock-solid.** Every one of the 7 directly verifiable constraints passes on 100% of assignments. The solver is producing legal, absence-respecting, properly-rested plans.
2. **Partitioning + Phase I carryover + sub-partitioning all exercise cleanly.** 4 partitions, 2 sub-partitioned at the 200-demand threshold, zero `[DATE-OVERLAP]` warnings, Phase K `LC_08 SKIPPED` gate firing on every partition, no duplicate RT/CT rows in the merged output (Fix A dedupe held).
3. **Recommendations 1 and 2** (skill gaps, location imbalance) are genuinely actionable and specific — they're the best pieces of the analyzer surface.
4. **CP-SAT search terminates cleanly** under 400s wall time for a ~600-demand / 49-resource / 34-day scope with 15 constraints + ~2,334 policy soft violations tracked — well within the 1,800s limit.

### 9.2 Instrumentation gaps (priority 1)

